      <section eId="sec_CC-2362-1">
        <num>CC 2362.1</num>
        <heading>2362.1.  Obligation incurred in an action for divorce</heading>
        <subsection eId="CC-2362-1__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>An obligation incurred before the date of a judgment of divorce for attorney fees
and costs in an action for divorce and in incidental actions is deemed to be a community
obligation.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-2362-1__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The obligation for attorney fees and costs incurred by the perpetrator of abuse or
awarded against him in an action for divorce granted pursuant to Article 103</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CC-2362-1__subsec_B__subsec_4">
            <num>(4)</num>
            <content>
              <p>or</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CC-2362-1__subsec_B__subsec_5">
            <num>(5)</num>
            <content>
              <p>or in
an action in which the court determines that a spouse or a child of one of the spouses was the
victim of domestic abuse committed by the perpetrator during the marriage, and in incidental
actions, shall be a separate obligation of the perpetrator.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109437</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
